      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to rule any of these out. POMPEII EMPIRE (6) is an SA galloper with a good record here and returns from a break. Has won fresh and well placed this class. Could be over the odds. LIMITED RISK (8) resumed from a long break in town in Adelaide and wasn't beaten far. Fitter and will find this easier. Go well off the low draw. VERBOSITY (4) was a winner four back then placed last three. Continues to race well and is back in grade for this. Leading chance. MODS (9) is a progressive type and hard to knock recent form here, scoring the last two. Lifted strongly to land the prize latest and can measure up again. FRAWLEY (3) is fitter for two runs back and is a strong contender on best.",
